article.description: Jordan Dartis was 6 of 12 from long range for 22 points as Ohio remained undefeated, knocking off Tennessee Tech 68-57 on Friday night.
article.headline: Dartis hits 6 treys, leads Ohio to 68-57 win over Tenn. Tech
article.linkText: Dartis hits 6 treys, leads Ohio to 68-57 win over Tenn. Tech
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio -- Jordan Dartis was 6 of 12 from long range for 22 points as Ohio remained undefeated, knocking off Tennessee Tech 68-57 on Friday night. Dartis hit just one shot that was not a 3-pointer, making 7 of 16 from the floor. Jason Carter added 17 points and had three blocks, Jaaron Simmons had 12 points while dishing out seven assists and Antonio Campbell grabbed 10 rebounds. The Bobcats have started with a 4-0 record for the first time since the 2012-13 season when they began 6-0 and went on to earn a Mid-American Conference co-championship. Tennessee Tech sprinted out to a 20-11 lead midway in the first half and was still up 24-21 at the 6:47 mark. Dartis nailed a 3-pointer to tie and Campbell slammed home a dunk to take the lead for good, 26-24, with 2:33 left in the first half. Aleksa Jugovic had 20 points to lead Tennessee Tech (1-5).
